WEBVTT

00:00:00.850 --> 00:00:05.849
Jehovah highly values the loyalty of his worshipers.

00:00:05.849 --> 00:00:12.849
He especially appreciates it when we are loyal to him even under adversity.

00:00:12.849 --> 00:00:17.850
How does Jehovah respond when we remain loyal to him?

00:00:17.850 --> 00:00:23.850
He in turn takes great pleasure in showing his loyalty to us.

00:00:24.850 --> 00:00:28.850
Psalm 145 verse 17 says,

00:00:28.850 --> 00:00:33.850
Jehovah is loyal in all that he does.

00:00:33.850 --> 00:00:39.850
This means that Jehovah is dependable, always faithful.

00:00:39.850 --> 00:00:43.850
He will never abandon his friends.

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:48.850
How do you feel about having Jehovah on your side?

00:00:48.850 --> 00:00:53.159
There is no greater blessing.

00:00:53.159 --> 00:01:00.159
Jehovah is willing and able to use his limitless power in behalf of his people.

00:01:00.159 --> 00:01:04.159
So it makes sense to be on Jehovah's side.

00:01:04.159 --> 00:01:14.159
For that reason most, if not all of Jehovah's worshipers, start out with every intention of being loyal to him.

00:01:14.159 --> 00:01:19.159
But there is a difference between wanting to be loyal to God,

00:01:19.159 --> 00:01:26.159
claiming to be loyal to God, and actually remaining loyal to God.

00:01:26.159 --> 00:01:31.159
Every one of us will have our loyalty to Jehovah put to the test.

00:01:31.159 --> 00:01:38.159
When that happens, will you take a firm stand on Jehovah's side?

00:01:38.159 --> 00:01:45.159
The issue of loyalty is clearly illustrated by the events that took place in the wilderness of Sinai,

00:01:45.159 --> 00:01:49.159
shortly after the Israelites left Egypt.

00:01:49.159 --> 00:01:54.159
God's people started out with every intention of being loyal to Jehovah.

00:01:54.159 --> 00:01:59.159
They entered into a covenant in which they promised to be loyal to God.

00:01:59.159 --> 00:02:05.159
And Jehovah in turn offered them his unbreakable loyalty.

00:02:05.159 --> 00:02:08.159
What lessons can we learn from this account?

00:02:08.159 --> 00:02:14.159
Let us start by reading Exodus 20 verses 1 through 7.

00:02:14.159 --> 00:02:19.789
Then God spoke all these words.

00:02:19.789 --> 00:02:27.789
I am Jehovah your God, who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.

00:02:27.789 --> 00:02:32.789
