Moses and the Levites were unquestionably

00:19:16.539 --> 00:19:18.539
on Jehovah's side.

00:19:18.539 --> 00:19:20.539
In response,

00:19:20.539 --> 00:19:23.539
Jehovah proved loyal to them.

00:19:23.539 --> 00:19:28.539
Jehovah was also loyal to his friends, Abraham, Isaac and Jacob,

00:19:28.539 --> 00:19:31.539
by remembering the promises he had made to them.

00:19:31.539 --> 00:19:35.539
So he did not exterminate the entire nation.

00:19:35.539 --> 00:19:42.779
Jehovah is indeed on the side of those who are loyal to him.

00:19:42.779 --> 00:19:46.779
Please follow along as we conclude our Bible reading.

00:19:46.779 --> 00:19:50.779
Let us now read Exodus chapter 34

00:19:50.779 --> 00:19:56.470
verses 1 through 14.

00:19:56.470 --> 00:19:58.470
Then, Jehovah said to Moses,

00:19:58.470 --> 00:20:03.470
Carve out for yourself two tablets of stone like the first ones.

00:20:03.470 --> 00:20:07.470
And I will write on the tablets the words that appeared on the first tablets,

00:20:07.470 --> 00:20:09.470
which you shatter.

00:20:09.470 --> 00:20:11.470
Get ready for the morning,

00:20:11.470 --> 00:20:14.470
as you will go up in the morning to Mount Sinai

00:20:14.470 --> 00:20:18.470
and station yourself before me there on the top of the mountain.

00:20:19.470 --> 00:20:22.470
But nobody may go up with you.

00:20:22.470 --> 00:20:26.470
And nobody else should be seen anywhere on the mountain.

00:20:26.470 --> 00:20:32.470
Not even the flocks or herds should graze in front of that mountain.

00:20:32.470 --> 00:20:37.470
So Moses carved out two tablets of stone like the first ones.

00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:41.470
And got up early in the morning and went up Mount Sinai

00:20:41.470 --> 00:20:44.470
just as Jehovah had commanded him.

00:20:44.470 --> 00:20:47.470
And he took the two tablets of stone in his hand.

00:20:48.470 --> 00:20:51.470
Then, Jehovah came down in the cloud,

00:20:51.470 --> 00:20:54.470
and stationed himself with him there,

00:20:54.470 --> 00:20:57.470
and declared the name of Jehovah.

00:20:57.470 --> 00:21:00.470
Jehovah was passing before him and declaring,

00:21:00.470 --> 00:21:02.470
Jehovah.

00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:07.470
Jehovah, a God merciful and compassionate,

00:21:07.470 --> 00:21:12.470
slow to anger and abundant in loyal love and truth,

00:21:12.470 --> 00:21:15.470
showing loyal love to thousands,

00:21:15.470 --> 00:21:19.470
pardoning error and transgression and sin,

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:23.470
but he will by no means leave the guilty unpunished,

00:21:23.470 --> 00:21:29.470
bringing punishment for the error of fathers upon sums and upon grandsons,

00:21:29.470 --> 00:21:34.470
upon the third generation and upon the fourth generation.

00:21:34.470 --> 00:21:39.470
Moses hurried to bow low to the earth and prostrate himself.

00:21:39.470 --> 00:21:41.470
Then he said,

00:21:42.470 --> 00:21:46.470
If now I have found favor in your eyes,

00:21:46.470 --> 00:21:50.470
or Jehovah, then please, Jehovah,

00:21:50.470 --> 00:21:53.470
go along with us in our midst,

00:21:53.470 --> 00:21:57.470
although we are an obstinate people,

00:21:57.470 --> 00:22:01.470
and forgive our error and our sin,

00:22:01.470 --> 00:22:05.470
and take us as your own possession.

00:22:05.470 --> 00:22:07.470
In turn, he said,

00:22:07.470 --> 00:22:10.470
Here I am making a covenant.

00:22:10.470 --> 00:22:12.470
Before all your people,

00:22:12.470 --> 00:22:16.470
I will do wonderful things that have never been done

00:22:16.470 --> 00:22:19.470
in all the earth or among all the nations,

00:22:19.470 --> 00:22:24.470
and all the people among whom you live will see the work of Jehovah,

00:22:24.470 --> 00:22:28.470
for it is an awe-inspiring thing that I am doing with you.

00:22:28.470 --> 00:22:32.470
Pay attention to what I am commanding you today.

00:22:32.470 --> 00:22:35.470
Here I am driving out from before you,

00:22:35.470 --> 00:22:39.470
the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Hittites,

00:22:39.470 --> 00:22:42.470
the Parasites, the Highvites,

00:22:42.470 --> 00:22:44.470
and the Jebusites.

00:22:44.470 --> 00:22:49.470
Be careful that you do not make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land

00:22:49.470 --> 00:22:51.470
to which you are going,

00:22:51.470 --> 00:22:54.470
or it may prove to be a snare among you,

00:22:54.470 --> 00:22:57.470
but you are to pull down their alters,

00:22:57.470 --> 00:23:00.470
or to shatter their sacred pillars,

00:23:00.470 --> 00:23:04.470
and their sacred poles you are to cut down.

00:23:04.470 --> 00:23:08.470
You must not bow down to another God.

00:23:08.470 --> 00:23:13.470
For Jehovah is known for requiring exclusive devotion.

00:23:13.470 --> 00:23:18.470
Yes, he is a God who requires exclusive devotion.

00:23:18.470 --> 00:23:26.730
What lesson do we learn from this Bible account?

00:23:26.730 --> 00:23:31.730
Wanting to be loyal to Jehovah is not enough.

00:23:31.730 --> 00:23:34.730
This world's corrupting influences can deceive us

00:23:34.730 --> 00:23:38.730
into thinking that we can deviate from Jehovah's principles

00:23:38.730 --> 00:23:41.730
and still be loyal to him.

00:23:41.730 --> 00:23:46.730
But Jehovah requires exclusive devotion.

00:23:46.730 --> 00:23:49.730
Granted, we will face adversities.

00:23:49.730 --> 00:23:53.730
We might have unexpected family problems

00:23:53.730 --> 00:23:57.730
or encounter serious financial difficulties.

00:23:57.730 --> 00:24:01.730
Members of the congregation may offend us.

00:24:01.730 --> 00:24:06.730
Poor health may cause us great suffering.

00:24:06.730 --> 00:24:09.730
When experiencing such distress,

00:24:09.730 --> 00:24:14.730
we must always remember that violating Jehovah's principles

00:24:14.730 --> 00:24:17.730
is never a solution.

00:24:17.730 --> 00:24:20.730
But taking a firm stand on Jehovah's side

00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:24.730
will always bring blessings.

00:24:24.730 --> 00:24:26.730
This is guaranteed

00:24:26.730 --> 00:24:34.730
because Jehovah is always dependable, reliable, and unfailing.

00:24:34.730 --> 00:24:37.730
He promises to show loyal love

00:24:37.730 --> 00:24:41.730
to those who give him exclusive devotion.

00:24:41.730 --> 00:24:44.730
In effect, Jehovah is telling us,

00:24:44.730 --> 00:24:47.730
if you prove to be on my side,

00:24:47.730 --> 00:24:50.730
I will prove to be on your side.

00:24:50.730 --> 00:24:53.730
As we just read,

00:24:53.730 --> 00:24:57.730
Jehovah will do wonderful things for his people.

00:24:57.730 --> 00:25:01.730
Jehovah is a God merciful and compassionate,

00:25:01.730 --> 00:25:03.730
slow to anger,

00:25:03.730 --> 00:25:07.730
and abundant in loyal love.
